fields.name: Vobster Quay
fields.facilities:
Good training site, good for SD & DL. Not great for OD few shallow training areas. 
Changing facilities, shop, kit hire, burger van. 
Vis generally good (better than Stoney not as good as Capernwray).
Maximum depth 36m
Underwater atractions include boat, caravan, plane and tunnel.

fields.name: HMS Scylla
fields.facilities:
Leander class frigate sunk in 2003. Now successful artificial reef, covered in corals and sponges. 

Max depth 24m

fields.name: James Eagan Layne
fields.facilities:
WWII Liberty ship sunk March 1945, cargo of various goods which can still be seen. 

A huge wreck and very popular, becoming quite broken up. 

7 - 24m depth

fields.name: Puffin Divers
fields.facilities:
Dive shop, hire centre, fill station. 

Launch for boats, slopping shore dive, not a great dive but good for a check out dive.

fields.name: Nemo 33
fields.facilities:
One of the deepest pools in the world. Deepest point 33m. 

All the usual facilities you would expect a pool to have. Good restaurant, dive shop ok. 

Pool itself is fun deep 33m pit most of pool around 10m with tunnel between the two sections.

fields.name: Weasel Loch
fields.facilities:
Shore dive, back of Eyemouth Holiday park, down wooden steps then over rocks. 

Can be difficult entry especially at low tide. 

Max depth approx 12m.
